  "content": "a vague direction to a complete design.\n  </div>\n\n  <!-- Exploration cards -->\n  <div style=\"font-size: 15px; font-weight: 700; letter-spacing: 2px; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--accent-cyan); margin-bottom: 16px;\">Three Approaches Explored</div>\n  <div style=\"display: flex; gap: 16px; margin-bottom: 20px;\">\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--text-muted); border-radius: 16px; padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px;\">A: Score-Based Decay</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;\">Fixed thresholds. Simple. But no way to promote knowledge that becomes relevant again.</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--accent-red); font-weight: 600; margin-top: 8px;\">Rejected: too rigid</div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--text-muted); border-radius: 16px; padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px;\">B: Usage-Driven Tiering</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;\">Promotion paths based on access. Flexible. But no decay for unused entries.</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--accent-red); font-weight: 600; margin-top: 8px;\">Rejected: no forgetting</div>\n    </div>\n    <div style=\"flex: 1; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-top: 4px solid var(--accent-green); border-radius: 16px; padding: 20px;\">\n      <div style=\"font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 8px;\">C: Hybrid + Policies</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 16px; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6;\">Composite scoring with configurable forgetting. Both decay and promotion.</div>\n      <div style=\"font-size: 15px; color: var(--accent-green); font-weight: 600; margin-top: 8px;\">Selected: best of both</div>\n    </div>\n  </div>",
